mples of common sense behavior that we hope will help you to make life safer and more secure  Personal Safety Awareness Though it is hard to think about  summer is over and cadets have returned to school  Hundreds of young adults have arrived from all over the county  either for the first time  or to embark on another semester  While the new semester brings opportunities and excitement  there is still the potential to be a victim of crime  Below are some tips for young adults while they are spending time both on and off Post  Use the buddy system  Don t walk alone if possible  especially at night  Report any suspicious activity observed on Post to the VMI Police or Lexington Police  It may turn out to be nothing  but why risk it  Stay in well lighted areas while walking at night  and entering and exiting buildings  If an area feels unsafe  chances are that others feel the same way  Inform the police and let them help make things safer on your Post  Be alert to what goes on around Post  The email notifications of criminal activity around Post may seem annoying  but being aware of what is going on out there is the first step in making sure that you don t get caught in the middle of it  Use good judgment when consuming alcohol  Remember that excessive drinking can lower your inhibitions and affect your judgment  increasing the risk of injury or victimization  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 